GCP Account with billing enabled
Google Cloud SDK installed
Terraform installed

Step 1: Set Up GCP Authentication

*******TO CREATE SERVICE ACCOUNT 
gcloud iam service-accounts create terraform-sa --display-name "Terraform Service Account"

*******Project ID to be created earlier before applying the below command:
gcloud projects add-iam-policy-binding <PROJECT_ID> --member="serviceAccount:terraform-sa@<PROJECT_ID>.iam.gserviceaccount.com" --role="roles/owner"

******Create and Download Key:
gcloud iam service-accounts keys create terraform-key.json \
  --iam-account=terraform-sa@YOUR_PROJECT_ID.iam.gserviceaccount.com

Step 2: Create Terraform Configuration Structure
terraform-gcp/
├── main.tf
├── variables.tf
├── outputs.tf
├── terraform.tfvars
└── providers.tf

*********Initialize and Apply Terraform
terraform init
*********Validate Configuration:
terraform validate
**********Plan the Deployment:
terraform plan
*********Apply the Configuration:
terraform apply
Type yes when prompted to confirm.
*********Verify Deployment:
# List buckets to verify creation
gsutil ls

# Check bucket details
gsutil ls -L gs://your-bucket-name

*******Clean Up Resources
terraform destroy

